<paragraph id="8BFC8B414726FFDEFF4E677DFA8809C6" blockId="3.[151,1436,944,1799]" pageId="3" pageNumber="167">
<emphasis id="B93757534726FFDEFF4E677DFEAA092A" bold="true" box="[199,315,1593,1619]" pageId="3" pageNumber="167">Remarks.</emphasis>
The male genitalia of this species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C43F0C24726FFDEFCCC677EFBA9092A" authorityName="Mahmood &amp; Ahmed" authorityYear="1969" box="[837,1080,1593,1619]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Benglebra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="167" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alami" subGenus="Benglebra">
<emphasis id="B93757534726FFDEFCCC677EFCF5092A" box="[837,868,1594,1619]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="167">M.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="B93757534726FFDEFCFA677DFC79092A" box="[883,1000,1593,1619]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="167">Benglebra</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="B93757534726FFDEFC71677DFBA9092A" box="[1016,1080,1593,1619]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="167">alami</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but differs as follows: (1) male pygofer with a long spine arising from middle of ventral margin and recurved subapically (
<figureCitation id="137897C44726FFDEFB216719FABA090E" box="[1192,1323,1629,1655]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–24" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1743,1768]" captionTargetBox="[240,1347,179,1713]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[240,1347,179,1714]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 13–24. M. (Benglebra) curvata sp. nov., male 13. Male habitus, dorsal view; 14. Male habitus, lateral view; 15. Head and thorax, lateral view; 16. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 17. Face; 18. Style, dorsal view; 19. Valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; 20. Shaft, caudal view; 21. Male pygofer, lateral view; 22. Connective and aedeagus, dorsal view; 23. Connective and aedeagus, lateral view; 24. Male pygofer, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (13–17); 0.2 mm (18–24)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3346435/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="167">Figs 21, 24</figureCitation>
) (pygofer with inner stout spines, not recurved subapically in 
<taxonomicName id="4C43F0C24726FFDEFD5D67C6FC5709E2" authorityName="Mahmood &amp; Ahmed" authorityYear="1969" box="[724,966,1665,1691]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Benglebra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="167" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alami" subGenus="Benglebra">
<emphasis id="B93757534726FFDEFD5D67C6FD6209E2" box="[724,755,1666,1691]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="167">M.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="B93757534726FFDEFC8B67C5FCE609E2" box="[770,887,1665,1691]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="167">Benglebra</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="B93757534726FFDEFC0F67C5FC5709E2" box="[902,966,1665,1691]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="167">alami</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); (2) aedeagus with smooth dorsal margin in lateral view (
<figureCitation id="137897C44726FFDEFECF67E1FE5709C6" box="[326,454,1701,1727]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–24" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1743,1768]" captionTargetBox="[240,1347,179,1713]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[240,1347,179,1714]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 13–24. M. (Benglebra) curvata sp. nov., male 13. Male habitus, dorsal view; 14. Male habitus, lateral view; 15. Head and thorax, lateral view; 16. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 17. Face; 18. Style, dorsal view; 19. Valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; 20. Shaft, caudal view; 21. Male pygofer, lateral view; 22. Connective and aedeagus, dorsal view; 23. Connective and aedeagus, lateral view; 24. Male pygofer, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (13–17); 0.2 mm (18–24)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3346435/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="167">Figs 22–23</figureCitation>
) (aedeagus with serrated dorsal margin near apex in 
<taxonomicName id="4C43F0C24726FFDEFB9F67E2FA9809C6" authorityName="Mahmood &amp; Ahmed" authorityYear="1969" box="[1046,1289,1701,1727]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Benglebra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="167" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alami" subGenus="Benglebra">
<emphasis id="B93757534726FFDEFB9F67E2FBA409C6" box="[1046,1077,1702,1727]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="167">M.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="B93757534726FFDEFBCD67E1FB2809C6" box="[1092,1209,1701,1727]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="167">Benglebra</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="B93757534726FFDEFB4067E1FA9809C6" box="[1225,1289,1701,1727]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="167">alami</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFC8B414726FFDEFF4E678DFED9087E" blockId="3.[151,1436,944,1799]" pageId="3" pageNumber="167">
<emphasis id="B93757534726FFDEFF4E678DFEDF099A" bold="true" box="[199,334,1737,1763]" pageId="3" pageNumber="167">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name is derived from the Latin word “curvata”, referring to the subapically curved pygofer ventral process.
</paragraph>
